<subsection><title>Example 2: Using <tag>cell</tag> with border and alignment attributes </title>
<p>In the code below, the <attr>right</attr>, <attr>bottom</attr>,  and <attr>halign</attr> attributes are used with the <tag>cell</tag> component.  Valid values for the <attr>halign</attr> attribute are: <c>"left", "center", "justify",</c> and <c>"right"</c> and the default value is <c>"left"</c>.  If an attribute is specified in both a parent and a child component, the styling specified by the child component governs. (See also <ref uri="doenet:doenetId=zRuXlzQ0_iNqNqZHHQMxG"><tag>table</tag></ref>, <ref uri="doenet:doenetId=Bm5kSKo8GvPyl85lokH8_"><tag>tabular</tag></ref>, <ref uri="doenet:doenetId=5HERf7liZuJ_-NnhzeTaU"><tag>title</tag></ref>.)</p>
<example boxed="true"><title>Sample DoenetML code (Example 2)</title>  
<pre>
&lt;table&gt;&lt;title&gt;Nonsense emoji shuffle&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;tabular width="500" height="300" bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium"&gt;
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell right="major"&gt;🔴&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell halign="center"&gt;🔵&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell bottom="minor"&gt;🟢&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
    
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell right="major"&gt;🟢&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell halign="right"&gt;🟣&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell bottom="minor"&gt;🔵&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
    
    &lt;row&gt;
      &lt;cell right="major"&gt;🟠&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔴&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell bottom="minor"&gt;🟣&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
  &lt;/tabular&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
</pre>
        </example>
      </subsection>
 
<!--*******************************************************-->
 

<example><title>What Doenet Renders (Example 2)</title>
